### ===== SHORTEST PATH TESTS =====

### Test 1: Simple Direct Path
### Expected: Gateway -> Router_A (total: 5.0)
POST http://localhost:9000/api/routes/shortest/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source": "Gateway",
  "destination": "Router_A"
}

### Test 2: Two-Hop Path
### Expected: Gateway -> Router_A -> Router_B (total: 8.0)
POST http://localhost:9000/api/routes/shortest/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source": "Gateway",
  "destination": "Router_B"
}

### Test 3: Three-Hop Path
### Expected: Gateway -> Router_A -> Router_C (total: 11.0)
POST http://localhost:9000/api/routes/shortest/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source": "Gateway",
  "destination": "Router_C"
}

### Test 4: Path to Switch
### Expected: Gateway -> Router_A -> Switch_1 (total: 7.0)
POST http://localhost:9000/api/routes/shortest/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source": "Gateway",
  "destination": "Switch_1"
}

### Test 5: Path to Server
### Expected: Gateway -> Router_A -> Switch_1 -> Server_X (total: 8.0)
POST http://localhost:9000/api/routes/shortest/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source": "Gateway",
  "destination": "Server_X"
}

### Test 6: Path to Database (Multiple Options)
### Expected: Gateway -> Router_A -> Switch_1 -> Database (total: 8.5)
### Alternative: Gateway -> Router_B -> Switch_2 -> Database (total: 12.5)
POST http://localhost:9000/api/routes/shortest/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source": "Gateway",
  "destination": "Database"
}

### Test 7: Router to Router Path
### Expected: Router_A -> Router_B (total: 3.0)
POST http://localhost:9000/api/routes/shortest/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source": "Router_A",
  "destination": "Router_B"
}

### Test 8: Router to Server Path
### Expected: Router_B -> Switch_2 -> Server_Y (total: 3.5)
POST http://localhost:9000/api/routes/shortest/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source": "Router_B",
  "destination": "Server_Y"
}

### Test 9: Server to Server Path
### Expected: Server_X -> Server_Y (total: 4.0)
POST http://localhost:9000/api/routes/shortest/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source": "Server_X",
  "destination": "Server_Y"
}

### Test 10: Complex Multi-Hop Path
### Expected: Router_A -> Router_C -> Switch_2 -> Server_Y (total: 11.0)
POST http://localhost:9000/api/routes/shortest/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source": "Router_A",
  "destination": "Server_Y"
}

### Test 11: Alternative Path Comparison
### Expected: Gateway -> Router_A -> Router_C (total: 11.0)
### Alternative: Gateway -> Router_C (total: 12.0) - should choose shorter path
POST http://localhost:9000/api/routes/shortest/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source": "Gateway",
  "destination": "Router_C"
}

### Test 12: Switch to Database Path
### Expected: Switch_1 -> Database (total: 1.5)
POST http://localhost:9000/api/routes/shortest/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source": "Switch_1",
  "destination": "Database"
}


### ===== NETWORK ANALYSIS =====

### View All Nodes
GET http://localhost:9000/api/nodes/

### View All Edges
GET http://localhost:9000/api/edges/

### View Route History
GET http://localhost:9000/api/routes/history/

### ===== PATH ANALYSIS SUMMARY =====
###
### Network Topology (Unidirectional):
### Gateway -> Router_A (5.0), Router_B (8.0), Router_C (12.0)
### Router_A -> Router_B (3.0), Router_C (6.0), Switch_1 (2.0)
### Router_B -> Router_C (4.0), Switch_2 (2.5)
### Router_C -> Switch_1 (3.0), Switch_2 (2.0)
### Switch_1 -> Server_X (1.0), Database (1.5)
### Switch_2 -> Server_Y (1.0), Database (2.0)
### Server_X -> Server_Y (4.0)
###
### Expected Shortest Paths:
### 1. Gateway -> Router_A: 5.0
### 2. Gateway -> Router_B: 8.0 (via Gateway -> Router_A -> Router_B)
### 3. Gateway -> Router_C: 11.0 (via Gateway -> Router_A -> Router_C)
### 4. Gateway -> Switch_1: 7.0 (via Gateway -> Router_A -> Switch_1)
### 5. Gateway -> Server_X: 8.0 (via Gateway -> Router_A -> Switch_1 -> Server_X)
### 6. Gateway -> Database: 8.5 (via Gateway -> Router_A -> Switch_1 -> Database)
### 7. Router_A -> Router_B: 3.0
### 8. Router_B -> Server_Y: 3.5 (via Router_B -> Switch_2 -> Server_Y)
### 9. Server_X -> Server_Y: 4.0
### 10. Router_A -> Server_Y: 11.0 (via Router_A -> Router_C -> Switch_2 -> Server_Y)
### 11. Gateway -> Router_C: 11.0 (shorter than direct 12.0)
### 12. Switch_1 -> Database: 1.5